 NVIDIA is looking for a senior software engineer to design, develop, and improve its visualization tools and technologies for the Autonomous Driving Software Group. The DRIVE UX team work with various groups within NVIDIA such as Graphics Processors, Mobile Processors, Deep Learning, and Artificial Intelligence to bring the best user interfaces and data visualization for both developers and automotive customers. Come join us and make a difference!
 What You'll be doing
 Architect, design, and write software with minimal mentorship.
 Work closely with the rest of the team to ensure that tasks are designed and completed in an efficient fashion.
 Review code, write design documents, outline use-cases, and develop test-plans.
 Work on challenging problems in areas of streaming video and data, API development, graphics drivers, embedded device optimization, and distributed system deployment.
 Optimize and harden the full stack of existing code ranging from graphics libraries up to user-level applications.
 Have fun solving challenges side-by-side with a top talent team.
 What we need to see:
 BS/MS in Computer Science or Computer Engineering or an equivalent experience
 5+ years of relevant experience.
 Strong object-oriented and template programming background, with C++ strongly preferred.
 Must have experience with rendering enginesâ€”both low-level immediate mode and high-level scene graphâ€”and managing resources such as memory, CPU, and GPU.
 As our team works with people around the world we require candidates who communicate excellently, both in writing and speaking.
 You will be developing and debugging multi-process applications and systems, on Windows and Linux desktop environments, as well as embedded systems.
 For senior developers we expect to see experience with CI/CD systems, a familiarity with containers, and a professional demeanor.
 We value our multifaceted team, and are always looking for candidates who bring extra talent in related areas. Have you worked on computer algorithms and can demonstrate the ability to choose the best possible to nail tricky problems? How about a background in design, implementation and deployment of real-time UI/UX/AR/VR graphics systems? Or perhaps you have experience with CUDA, OpenGL, and Vulkan. Let us know what you are capable of!
